HEADWORD: Blubbering
<hw>Blub"ber*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of weeping
noisily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He spake well save that his <qex>blubbering</qex> interrupted
him.</q> <rj><qau>Winthrop.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blubbery</ent>⟦br⟧
